    <name>
				<text>35.2.3.3 Defective articles (NOT IN QUIZ)</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<h4 class="HELM_exercise"> Exercise </h4>
<p> A <strong>lot</strong>&nbsp;consists of \({@gd@}\) good articles, \({@mnd@}\) articles with only minor defects and \({@mjd@}\) with major defects. One article is chosen at random from the lot.</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li> If \(G\) is the event that the article has no defects, find \(\mathbb{P}(G)\). </li>
<li> If \(M\) is the event that the article has major defects, find \(\mathbb{P}(M')\). </li>
<li> Find the probability that the article is either good or has major defects. This event is denoted \(G\cup M\), so that we are seeking the probability \(\mathbb{P}(G\cup M)\).</li>
</ol>
<p> Give all probabilities as fractions, not decimals: </p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li> \(\mathbb{P}(G)=\quad\)[[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]] </li>
<li> \(\mathbb{P}(M')=\quad\)[[input:ans2]][[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]] </li>
<li> \(\mathbb{P}(G\cup M)=\quad\)[[input:ans3]][[validation:ans3]][[feedback:prt3]] </li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<h4 class="HELM_solution"> Solution </h4>
<p> The total number of articles is \({@gd@} + {@mnd@} + {@mjd@} = {@enn@}\). </p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li> Only the \({@gd@}\) good articles have no defects, therefore \( \mathbb{P}(G) = {@gd@} / {@enn@} = {@ta1@} \). </li>
<li> The event \(M'\) corresponds to the article having no major defects, this occurs if we pick one of the \( {@gd@} \) good articles or one of the \( {@mnd@} \) articles with only minor defects, therefore \(\mathbb{P}(M') = ({@gd@} + {@mnd@}) / {@enn@} = {@ta2@}\). </li>
<li> There are \( {@gd@} \) good articles and \( {@mjd@} \) articles with major defects, therefore \( \mathbb{P}(G\cup M) = ({@gd@} + {@mjd@}) / {@enn@} = {@ta3@}\).
</li></ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
